e stanford offers resources for building a separate mobile site including server side detection the central web servers detect and place mobile devices into four broad categories smart phone feature phone tablet or desktop code snippets if you need detection you can also use this detection code get more information on device detection from the separate sites for mobile service page frameworks if you build a separate mobile site you ll likely use a frameworks kit we recommend using jquery mobile and you can see examples of it in some of the case studies for more information see the frameworks page in this developer's toolkit you ll find examples of responsive design grids screen resolutions for different devices device detection methodologies code snippets for redirects queries and cookies server and client side scripts frameworks last modified mon 29 aug 2011 at 9 11 pages about this service overview what is mobile awareness mobile web options terminology accessibility reference websites case study stanford home and commencement pages case study mobile aware web project case study it open house site case study explorecourses case study it services catalog and documentation case study stanfordwho case study web forms service developer resources responsive design separate sites for mobile different url same url let users choose frameworks learn more literature technologies site checking tools find answers submit a helpsu request stanford answers footer links stanford university helpsu user login stanford university terms of use copyright complaints
